properties.abstract: While everywhere around various tones of Gneiss-grey dominate, on top of Pizzo Molare the rock is multi-coloured. There is a wide range of red and brownish schist, light grey limestone and shiny white sugary dolomite. The variety of rocks is also responsible for the many colours of the flowers you encounter along the trails. They go from the clear white to fiery orange of the lilies and the most brilliant deep blue of the gentians.
properties.subtitle: A sediment tooth surrounded by crystalline rock
properties.title: Molare - Pizzo Molare – Carì

segments.description: From the bus stop Molare (1488 m) go into the village and to the church, where the well-marked hiking trail towards Bassa di Nara begins. The path, in the beginning wide, narrows after the crossing of the creek at Fornace (1565 m) and ascends through the forest up to the bifurcation at the fountain in Chèrz. Continue to ascend to Alpe Nara, where you sometimes need to guess the path in the pasture. The final ascent to Bassa di Nara is more visible and easier to find.

photos.caption: Bassa di Nara; view down to Valle di Blenio
Alpe Nara and above Bassa di Nara

segments.title: Molare - Bassa di Narasa di Nara

segments.description: From Bassa di Nara (2123 m) go briefly towards Pizzo di Nara. Before the summit traverse its west face on blocks and scree to reach the grassy breach in the summit ridge at P. 2247. Without further difficulties, sometimes pathless, hike up to Bocchetta di Sasso Bianco (2404 m) with its prominent and very white rock formations. Now on a worn-out trail follow the ridge to the large summit cross of Pizzo Molare (2585 m).

photos.caption: From Bassa di Nara it gets stonier. In the foreground you see the trail to P. 2247; in the background is Pizzo Molare.

segments.title: Bassa di Nara - Pizzo Molare

segments.description: From the summit of Pizzo Molare a fairly comfortable trail leads northward on the ridge down to the saddle at P. 2414, where many paths and sheep tracks merge. Continue more or less pathless on the Blenio side to a wide plateau at ca. 2530 m, east of Punta di Stou, from whose northernmost edge a small, but distinct path goes steeply down. As soon as possible turn left and ascend through the valley between Punta di Stou and Piancabella to reach P. 2469. On the block ridge or on its right face below Pizzo Bareta hike to P. 2432, where you come across a new faint path. It leads to the wide saddle Sella di Ör Languosa (2359 m) with its high voltage power line, at first on the north, then on the south of the crest. Within minutes you reach, pathless, Rifugio Gana Rossa (2270 m). There is no warden, but everything you need to spend the night, if you want to.

photos.caption: On the bypass of Pizzo Bareta
The last minutes before Sella Ör di Languosa (to the right the power line masts), to the left below is Rifugio Gana Rossa.

segments.title: Pizzo Molare - Rifugio Gana Rossa

segments.description: From the Rifugio descend on a well-marked access trail to Segna and Alpe di Vignone at 1970 m. Now in a wide arc hike through the forest of Pesc Vert to Carì di Dentro and the bus stop at Carì (1622 m).
segments.title: Rifugio Gana Rossa - Carì
